WEBVTT

00:01.560 --> 00:02.561
3, 2...

00:02.600 --> 00:04.659
[SHOW THEME MUSIC]

00:04.700 --> 00:07.260
HERE WITH US TODAY IS
SUPERVISORY SPECIAL AGENT

00:07.300 --> 00:10.406
DAVID ROSSI, RENOWNED
AUTHOR AND CO-FOUNDER

00:10.440 --> 00:13.534
OF THE FBI's FAMED
BEHAVIORAL ANALYSIS UNIT.

00:13.580 --> 00:16.048
HIS LATEST BOOK,
"UNDERSTANDING EVIL,"

00:16.080 --> 00:19.516
IS AN IN-DEPTH PORTRAIT OF
THE SERIAL KILLER TOMMY YATES.

00:19.550 --> 00:20.744
THANKS FOR JOINING US,
AGENT ROSSI.

00:20.780 --> 00:22.042
MY PLEASURE, BRIAN.

00:22.090 --> 00:23.682
OF THE HUNDREDS OF MURDERERS

00:23.720 --> 00:24.812
THAT YOU'VE ENCOUNTERED,

00:24.850 --> 00:26.784
WHY DID YOU CHOOSE
TO WRITE ABOUT YATES?

00:26.820 --> 00:29.254
WITH HIM IT WAS PERSONAL.

00:29.290 --> 00:31.155
WELL, EVERY YEAR
ON YOUR BIRTHDAY,

00:31.190 --> 00:32.623
YOU WOULD VISIT
YATES IN PRISON,

00:32.660 --> 00:34.525
AND HE'D GIVE YOU
THE LOCATION OF A BODY

00:34.560 --> 00:36.198
OF ONE OF HIS VICTIMS.

00:36.230 --> 00:37.390
WHY IS THAT?

00:37.430 --> 00:40.331
TOMMY YATES WAS IN
AN 8-BY-6-FOOT CELL.

00:40.370 --> 00:44.101
EVERY SECOND OF HIS
LIFE WAS DICTATED.

00:44.140 --> 00:45.698
SO IT WAS A GAME TO HIM.

00:45.740 --> 00:47.674
IT WAS.
AND I PLAYED ALONG

00:47.710 --> 00:49.075
IN ORDER TO PROVIDE
CLOSURE

00:49.110 --> 00:50.577
TO THOSE FAMILIES.

00:50.610 --> 00:52.248
IT CAN'T BE EASY
TO FIND COMMON GROUND

00:52.280 --> 00:54.077
WITH A SADISTIC
MURDERER.

00:54.120 --> 00:55.314
HOW DID YOU DO THAT?

00:55.350 --> 00:56.715
OH, GOOD!
WE DIDN'T MISS IT.

00:56.750 --> 00:58.115
GARCIA: NOPE, JUST STARTED.

00:58.150 --> 00:59.253
ROSSI: YOU HAVE TO SHOW
RESPECT TO...

00:59.290 --> 01:00.814
WE'RE UP TO OUR
EYEBALLS IN CASES.

01:00.860 --> 01:02.555
THE GUY NEVER TAKES
A VACATION.

01:02.590 --> 01:04.683
I WANT TO KNOW WHEN
HE'D FIND THE TIME

01:04.730 --> 01:05.924
TO WRITE ANOTHER BOOK.

01:05.960 --> 01:09.726
SOMEONE MUST HAVE PUT
HIS MANDATORY 6 WEEKS
OFF TO GOOD USE.

01:09.770 --> 01:11.226
ANYBODY HEARD FROM TARA?

01:11.270 --> 01:12.794
OH, SHE'S FINISHING UP
WITH FLOYD FERELL.

01:12.840 --> 01:14.193
SHE'LL BE BACK IN D.C. SOON.

01:14.240 --> 01:15.389
I'M DVRing THIS
FOR HER AND REID.

01:15.440 --> 01:16.759
THEY DIDN'T WANT
TO MISS IT EITHER.

01:16.810 --> 01:19.335
OH, I HOPE HIS
FIRST NIGHT TEACHING
GOES WELL.

01:19.380 --> 01:21.507
HE WAS A LITTLE
NERVOUS ABOUT IT.

01:21.540 --> 01:23.849
BRIAN: THIS BOOK FEELS LIKE
IT'S PART MEMOIR,

01:23.880 --> 01:27.111
MORE SO THAN YOUR OTHERS.
IS THAT ONLY BECAUSE OF YATES?

01:27.150 --> 01:30.415
NOT NECESSARILY. SOME
OF IT WAS NECESSITY.

01:30.450 --> 01:32.452
HOW SO?

01:32.490 --> 01:33.559
WELL, I'VE SPENT
MY ENTIRE CAREER

01:33.590 --> 01:35.114
EXPLORING
OTHER PEOPLE'S MINDS,

01:35.160 --> 01:37.287
BUT VERY LITTLE TIME
EXPLORING MY OWN.

01:37.330 --> 01:39.525
AND WHAT DID YOU FIND?

01:39.560 --> 01:41.790
THAT OBSESSION
IS NOT NECESSARILY

01:41.830 --> 01:45.220
A PATH TRAVELED ONLY
BY SERIAL KILLERS.

01:45.270 --> 01:46.498
HOW COME?

01:46.540 --> 01:48.792
WELL, PROFILERS
AND SERIAL KILLERS

01:48.840 --> 01:52.173
OVERLAP IN MORE WAYS
THAN I WOULD HAVE
IMAGINED.

01:52.210 --> 01:54.132
WE'RE BOTH
MISSION-ORIENTED

01:54.180 --> 01:57.149
AND DRIVEN BY
NEED-BASED DESIRES.

01:57.180 --> 01:59.910
AND THE KEY DIFFERENCE
IS THAT WHILE THEY

01:59.950 --> 02:03.181
TAKE LIVES, WE DO OUR
BEST TO PRESERVE THEM,

02:03.220 --> 02:05.313
SORRY TO INTERRUPT,
BUT WE HAVE BREAKING NEWS.

02:05.350 --> 02:08.217
EARLIER TONIGHT WAS A THIRD
IN WHAT MIAMI POLICE

02:08.260 --> 02:11.184
ARE CALLING A STRING
OF ROBBERY-MURDERS.

02:11.230 --> 02:15.223
IT STARTED LAST WEEK NEAR
CORAL GABLES UNIVERSITY.

02:15.260 --> 02:17.490
BUT I SHOULD WARN YOU IS,
WHAT YOU'RE ABOUT TO SEE

02:17.530 --> 02:19.361
COULD BE CONSIDERED GRAPHIC.

02:19.400 --> 02:23.234
[IN DISTINCT CHATTER,
SIRENS]

02:23.270 --> 02:26.273
OFFICER: KEEP IT BLOCKED
OFF. PLEASE, MA'AM.

02:26.310 --> 02:28.198
BRIAN: AGENT ROSSI,
WOULD YOU CARE TO COMMENT?

02:28.240 --> 02:31.471
I WOULD LIKE TO TALK
TO MIAMI POLICE
BEFORE DOING SO.

02:31.510 --> 02:33.546
I UNDERSTAND.
AGAIN, THE BOOK IS

02:33.580 --> 02:35.719
[CELL PHONE VIBRATES]
"UNDERSTANDING EVIL."

02:35.750 --> 02:37.342
SHE WAS PARKED WHEN THE UNSUB
CAME UP AND SHOT HER.

02:37.390 --> 02:38.812
SHE MIGHT NOT HAVE EVEN
SEEN HIM COMING.

02:38.850 --> 02:40.659
LOCALS JUST SENT OVER
THE DETAILS.

02:40.690 --> 02:42.487
THEY BELIEVE IT'S A SERIES
OF ROBBERY-HOMICIDES,

02:42.530 --> 02:44.828
BUT HE ONLY ROBBED
THE FIRST VICTIM.

02:44.860 --> 02:47.249
ROBBERY COULD BE
A FORENSIC COUNTERMEASURE

02:47.300 --> 02:49.598
TO TRY AND KEEP THE COPS
FROM TYING THE CASES TOGETHER.

02:49.630 --> 02:52.292
A BIG CITY LIKE MIAMI,
HOW DO WE EVEN KNOW
THEY'RE RELATED?

02:52.340 --> 02:55.195
BALLISTICS MATCH.
HE USED A .44-CALIBER.

02:55.240 --> 02:57.333
BOLD CHOICE.
THAT'S A BIG GUN.

02:57.370 --> 02:59.531
THEN THERE'S THE VICTIMS--
MAGGIE SWANSON,

02:59.580 --> 03:02.799
KATHERINE SHELTON,
AND NOW JEANNETTE CLAUSON.

03:02.850 --> 03:05.341
EACH SHOT ONCE IN THE HEART,
THEY DIED INSTANTLY.

03:05.380 --> 03:08.747
HE'S GOT A TYPE.
AND THE UNSUB COULD
BE A SCORNED LOVER.

03:08.780 --> 03:12.318
WE'RE GOING TO MEET DAVE
IN MIAMI. WHEELS UP IN 10.

03:19.600 --> 03:21.818
THAT PLACE WAS COOL,
RIGHT?

03:21.860 --> 03:23.259
YEAH.

03:23.300 --> 03:25.768
I TOOK MY SISTER
THERE ONCE.

03:25.800 --> 03:27.893
SHE WAS VISITING
FROM SEATTLE.

03:27.940 --> 03:29.760
WE HAD A REALLY
GOOD TIME.

03:29.810 --> 03:33.234
YOU TOOK ME TO THE SAME
PLACE YOU TOOK YOUR SISTER?

03:33.280 --> 03:35.908
WELL, UH, YEAH, BUT,

03:35.940 --> 03:40.309
I MEAN--I KNOW
HOW THAT SOUNDS.

03:40.350 --> 03:42.580
LOOK, I KNOW
THIS GREAT PUB

03:42.620 --> 03:44.315
NOT TOO FAR
FROM HERE.

03:44.350 --> 03:47.513
MAYBE NEXT TIME
INSTEAD OF JUST DINNER?

03:47.560 --> 03:50.279
UM, I SHOULD GO.

03:50.330 --> 03:54.289
UH, IT'S ONLY 9:30.

03:54.330 --> 03:56.469
YEAH, I'M SORRY. I JUST
HAVE AN EARLY MORNING.

03:56.500 --> 03:58.365
I'M SURE YOU DO, TOO.

03:58.400 --> 04:01.335
YEAH. DO YOU NEED
A RIDE?

04:01.370 --> 04:05.761
THANKS. I WOULD, BUT MY CAR
IS JUST DOWN THE STREET.

04:05.810 --> 04:09.371
WELL, WHY DON'T YOU
TEXT ME, THEN,
WHEN YOU GET HOME.

04:09.410 --> 04:10.877
SO I KNOW YOU'RE SAFE.

04:10.910 --> 04:11.945
OK?

04:11.980 --> 04:14.448
YEAH, OK.

04:17.020 --> 04:20.353
UH--IT WAS NICE
TO MEET YOU, STEVEN.

04:20.390 --> 04:21.482
GOOD NIGHT.

04:49.050 --> 04:51.416
[LINE RINGING]

04:51.450 --> 04:52.417
WOMAN: HELLO.

04:52.460 --> 04:53.484
HEY, IT'S ME.

04:53.520 --> 04:54.487
HOW'D IT GO?

04:54.520 --> 04:55.748
YEAH, I MEAN,
IT STARTED OFF OK,

04:55.790 --> 04:57.985
BUT, I DON'T KNOW,
IT JUST GOT WEIRD.

04:58.030 --> 04:59.895
I GOT THIS VIBE
FROM HIM.

04:59.930 --> 05:01.329
[TAPS ON WINDOW]

05:01.360 --> 05:02.497
YOU THINK YOU CAN
JUST BLOW ME OFF?

05:02.530 --> 05:03.724
WOMAN ON PHONE:
WHO IS THAT?

05:03.770 --> 05:04.998
STEVEN, IT'S NOT LIKE THAT.

05:05.030 --> 05:06.793
WHAT THE HELL
ARE YOU DOING?
WOMAN: NATALIE?

05:06.840 --> 05:08.398
NATALIE?
STOP IT,
STEVEN !

05:08.440 --> 05:09.668
NO.
OH, MY GOD.
WHO IS THAT?

05:09.710 --> 05:10.938
NO.

05:10.970 --> 05:12.403
NATALIE,
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

05:12.440 --> 05:13.407
STOP IT!
NO! YOU DON'T
GET TO TELL ME--

05:13.440 --> 05:14.600
[GUNSHOT]

05:14.640 --> 05:16.847
OH, MY GOD! NATALIE!
NATALIE!

05:16.880 --> 05:19.872
[NATALIE SCREAMING]

05:19.920 --> 05:21.512
[GUNSHOT]

05:56.850 --> 05:58.112
PRENTISS:
"THE SPECTACLE IS CAPITAL,

05:58.150 --> 06:01.608
ACCUMULATED TO THE POINT
WHERE IT BECOMES IMAGE."

06:01.660 --> 06:03.878
GUY DEBORD.

06:03.930 --> 06:05.886
ALL 3 VICTIMS
LIVED IN THE SAME AREA

06:05.930 --> 06:07.522
AND LED LOW-RISK LIFESTYLES.

06:07.560 --> 06:09.824
THE PHYSICAL TYPE IS
WHAT ATTRACTS HIM.

06:09.870 --> 06:12.566
THERE DOESN'T SEEM
TO BE ANY OTHER
OBVIOUS LINK ON PAPER.

06:12.600 --> 06:14.534
ALVEZ:
YEAH, THERE WERE NO RED FLAGS

06:14.570 --> 06:15.662
ON ANY OF THEIR
BACKGROUNDS.

06:15.700 --> 06:17.133
THEY WERE JUST LIVING
THEIR LIVES.

06:17.170 --> 06:19.104
WHICH IS MOSTLY JUST WORK
AND HANGING OUT WITH FRIENDS.

06:19.140 --> 06:21.005
MAGGIE LOVED CATS,
KATHERINE WAS A HIKER,

06:21.040 --> 06:22.769
AND JEANNETTE LOVED
THE RAMONES.

06:22.810 --> 06:25.574
BETTER GET IN LINE THERE,
BROTHER. WHO DOESN'T LOVE THEM?

06:25.610 --> 06:28.147
SORRY TO STARTLE YOU.
WE JUST GOT BUZZED BY MIAMI PD.

06:28.180 --> 06:29.818
CRIME-FIGHTERS, THERE'S
A BALLISTIC MATCH

06:29.850 --> 06:32.683
ON TWO MORE VICTIMS
THAT WERE SHOT TONIGHT.

06:32.720 --> 06:34.517
AND CHECK IT OUT--THE GIRL.

06:34.560 --> 06:36.585
SHE LOOKS JUST LIKE THE OTHERS,
IN THEIR 20$, BRUNETTE.

06:36.630 --> 06:38.689
GARCIA: YEAH,
NATALIE CORBIS WAS A NURSE,

06:38.730 --> 06:40.652
STEVEN O'MALLEY WAS
A MECHANICAL ENGINEER.

06:40.700 --> 06:42.497
BOTH WERE VERY WELL-LIKED,
AND ACCORDING TO FRIENDS

06:42.530 --> 06:44.498
ON SOCIAL MEDIA,
THEY WERE ON A FIRST DATE.

06:44.530 --> 06:46.566
WELL, THERE'S A COUPLE
OTHER FIRSTS HERE.

06:46.600 --> 06:49.569
TWO BODIES AT THE SAME TIME
AND ONE OF THEM'S MALE.

06:49.610 --> 06:51.737
SO WAS HE COLLATERAL
DAMAGE OR A TARGET?

06:51.770 --> 06:55.206
5 VICTIMS IN ONE WEEK,
3 IN THE LAST 12 HOURS.

06:55.240 --> 06:57.208
IT FEELS LIKE OUR UNSUB'S
ON A SPREE.

06:57.250 --> 06:59.047
PRENTISS: DAVE'S ALREADY
ON HIS WAY TO THE M.E.

06:59.080 --> 07:00.479
MATT, YOU AND I WILL
SET UP AT THE STATION.

07:00.520 --> 07:02.715
JJ, LUKE, GO TO
THE LATEST CRIME SCENE.

07:10.930 --> 07:15.219
SO STEVEN'S STANDING HERE,
NATALIE'S INSIDE THE CAR,

07:15.260 --> 07:18.229
BANG AND BANG.

07:18.270 --> 07:20.158
IT FEELS LIKE THEY WERE
SAYING GOOD NIGHT,

07:20.200 --> 07:22.737
BUT WE KNOW STEVEN
WASN'T GOING HOME WITH HER.

07:22.770 --> 07:24.738
THE UNSUB WOULDN'T
KNOW THAT.

07:24.770 --> 07:28.103
IF HE'S A JILTED LOVER,
HE'D SEE STEVEN
AS A SURROGATE,

07:28.140 --> 07:30.040
THE GUY WHO STOLE
HIS GIRL.

07:30.080 --> 07:31.570
IF HE HAD HIS HEART BROKEN
RECENTLY,

07:31.610 --> 07:33.214
THAT COULD BE THE REASON
FOR THE SPREE.

07:33.250 --> 07:35.548
MAYBE HIS EX GOT ENGAGED.

07:35.580 --> 07:37.616
OR PREGNANT. AND THAT'S
WHY HE'S LASHING OUT.

07:37.650 --> 07:39.618
SO TIME OF DEATH WAS

07:39.660 --> 07:41.013
JUST BEFORE THEY
WERE FOUND.

07:41.060 --> 07:42.209
IT WAS LIKE, WHAT,
5 MINUTES?

07:42.260 --> 07:43.659
NO, TWO.

07:43.690 --> 07:45.829
JEEZ, THIS GUY'S
CUTTING IT CLOSE.

07:45.860 --> 07:51.594
WELL, A .44 MAGNUM
HAS GOT A BIG BANG.

07:51.630 --> 07:53.734
MAYBE
THAT'S THE POINT.

07:53.770 --> 07:56.238
HE WANTS THE ATTENTION.

07:56.270 --> 07:58.932
LOUD GUN.
ATTRACT S A BIG CROWD.

07:58.970 --> 08:01.279
RIGHT?
ADDS TO HIS THRILL.

08:01.310 --> 08:04.700
YEAH. SO WOULD STICKING
AROUND TO WATCH HIS WORK.

08:04.750 --> 08:06.274
DON'T THINK OF HIM
AS A SPREE KILLER,

08:06.310 --> 08:07.868
THINK OF HIM
AS A FIRE-STARTER.

08:07.920 --> 08:11.242
THAT'S WHY NO ONE SEES
HIM FLEE THE SCENE.

08:11.290 --> 08:13.781
COULD BE A FIRST
RESPONDER.

08:13.820 --> 08:16.948
BUT POLICE,
PARAMEDICS, WITNESSES,

08:16.990 --> 08:18.651
THEY'D HAVE TO GIVE
A STATEMENT.

08:18.690 --> 08:20.794
YEAH, IF HE WAS ON
MORE THAN ONE POLICE REPORT,

08:20.830 --> 08:23.128
HE'D BE ON OUR RADAR.

08:23.170 --> 08:25.229
WELL, MAYBE HE STICKS
AROUND TO WATCH

08:25.270 --> 08:28.797
AND JUST DOESN'T DRAW
ATTENTION TO HIMSELF.

08:28.840 --> 08:31.661
THIS GUY HIDES
IN PLAIN SIGHT.

08:59.700 --> 09:02.703
[IN DISTINCT CHATTER]

09:02.740 --> 09:04.708
MAN: EXCUSE ME.
OVER HERE, PLEASE.

09:04.740 --> 09:07.038
[OVERLAPPING CONVERSATIONS]

09:07.080 --> 09:08.638
WOMAN: WHEN WILL YOU BE
RELEASING...

09:08.680 --> 09:10.102
SECOND WOMAN: WHY DID
THE POLICE CALL IN THE FBI?

09:10.150 --> 09:11.299
SECOND MAN: WHAT CAN YOU TELL US
ABOUT THE LATEST VICTIMS?

09:11.350 --> 09:12.874
HEY, IS IT SAFE
TO GO OUT AT NIGHT?

09:12.920 --> 09:14.842
WE APPRECIATE YOUR
INTEREST AND CONCERN,

09:14.880 --> 09:17.314
BUT THE FBI HAS NO COMMENT
AT THIS TIME.

09:17.350 --> 09:19.716
NO COMMENT?

09:19.760 --> 09:21.853
WALLENBERG: SORRY ABOUT
THE VULTURES OUTSIDE.

09:21.890 --> 09:24.256
WE'RE DOING EVERYTHING
WE CAN TO KEEP THEM AT BAY.

09:24.290 --> 09:26.758
IT'S OK. THEY'VE GOT
A JOB TO DO. SO DO WE.

09:26.800 --> 09:28.688
WE DID SOME INITIAL
INTERVIEWS WITH THE FAMILIES

09:28.730 --> 09:30.595
AND FOUND
SOMETHING INTERESTING.

09:30.630 --> 09:31.927
THIS GUY MIGHT BE--

09:31.970 --> 09:34.097
WHAT?

09:34.140 --> 09:36.802
AGAIN? EXCUSE ME.

09:36.840 --> 09:38.762
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:52.050 --> 09:54.052
HAIR CLIPS.

09:54.090 --> 09:55.978
WHAT ABOUT THEM?

09:56.020 --> 09:58.284
NO, ALL THE VICTIMS
ARE WEARING THEM.

09:58.330 --> 09:59.922
THEY'RE GENERIC.

09:59.960 --> 10:01.894
BUT THEY'RE ALL PLACED
IN THE SAME SPOT

10:01.930 --> 10:03.397
RIGHT HERE
BEHIND THE LEI-T EAR.

10:03.430 --> 10:05.227
OH, THAT MUST BE WHAT
DETECTIVE WALLENBERG

10:05.270 --> 10:06.897
FOUND OUT FROM
THE FAMILY INTERVIEWS.

10:06.940 --> 10:09.704
THE VICS DIDN'T WEAR THESE,
SO THE UNSUB PLACED THEM.

10:09.740 --> 10:11.332
RITUAL ASPECT WOULD KEEP
HIM AT THE SCENE LONGER,

10:11.370 --> 10:13.907
ESCALATE HIS RISK,
WHICH HE MAY GET OFF ON.

10:13.940 --> 10:15.976
AND GOING WITH LUKE'S THEORY,

10:16.010 --> 10:18.649
THE WOMAN HE PINES FOR
MAY WEAR SOMETHING
LIKE THIS.

10:18.680 --> 10:20.671
UM, THEY'RE
PRETTY DATED.

10:20.720 --> 10:22.881
I'M NOT SURE WE SHOULD
LIMIT IT TO ROMANCE.

10:22.920 --> 10:26.686
THESE FEEL MORE LIKE
SOMETHING A MOTHER
OR A TEACHER WOULD WEAR.

10:26.720 --> 10:28.210
IT'S ALSO STRANGE
HOW PRIVATE HE MADE IT.

10:28.260 --> 10:29.784
I MEAN, THE PLACEMENT
OF THESE CLIPS

10:29.830 --> 10:31.821
MAKES IT REALLY
DIFFICULT TO SEE.

10:31.860 --> 10:35.091
EVERYTHING HE DOES
IS TO BE SEEN.

10:35.130 --> 10:39.089
SO WHY IS THE UNSUB
HIDING THIS?

10:39.130 --> 10:40.791
WELL, LET'S CHECK
WITH THE MANUFACTURER
OF THOSE CLIPS,

10:40.840 --> 10:42.398
SEE WHERE THEY'RE SOLD.

10:42.440 --> 10:43.532
THAT COULD BE A GOOD
STARTING POINT.

10:43.570 --> 10:46.778
MY GUESS IS ONLINE
AND IN EVERY DRUGSTORE
ACROSS MIAMI.

10:46.810 --> 10:49.335
WELL, THE GOOD NEWS IS,
THEY'RE ONLY VISIBLE
IN OFFICIAL CSPs.

10:49.380 --> 10:51.177
THEY CAN'T BE SEEN ANYWHERE
IN MEDIA COVERAGE.

10:51.210 --> 10:52.916
GREAT.
THAT'LL BUY US SOME TIME

10:52.950 --> 10:55.874
BEFORE THE PUBLIC FINDS OUT.

10:55.920 --> 10:57.410
WHAT THE...

11:02.220 --> 11:04.780
HOW DOES
CHANNEL 3 KNOW?

11:04.830 --> 11:07.128
LET'S FIND OUT.

11:10.230 --> 11:13.393
THIS IS EXACTLY THE KIND
OF THING THAT WE NEEDED.

11:13.440 --> 11:15.135
GREAT WORK, KAL.

11:15.170 --> 11:16.398
MM-HMM.

11:16.440 --> 11:17.839
SO NOW
WE HAVE TO NAME HIM--

11:17.870 --> 11:20.304
SOMETHING EVOCATIVE,
LIKE SON OF SAM

11:20.340 --> 11:23.207
OR BTK OR ZODIAC.

11:23.250 --> 11:24.945
ANYONE?

11:24.980 --> 11:26.140
THE MIAMI MAULER?

11:26.180 --> 11:28.819
WHAT IS HE, AN ESCAPED
LION FROM THE ZOO?

11:28.850 --> 11:30.112
[LAUGHTER]

11:30.150 --> 11:32.880
WHAT DO YOU SEE?

11:34.490 --> 11:36.822
SHOT-OUT WINDOW.

11:36.860 --> 11:39.021
A NEON LIGHT.

11:40.160 --> 11:42.219
THE NEON TERROR

11:42.260 --> 11:44.820
STRIKES AGAIN.

11:44.870 --> 11:46.497
NAMING THE UNSUB
IS A GRAVE MISTAKE.

11:46.530 --> 11:48.464
IT ROMANTICIZES HIM
IN THE PUBLIC'S MIND

11:48.500 --> 11:51.003
AND IN TURN GIVES HIM
A SENSE OF POWER AND CONTROL

11:51.040 --> 11:52.507
HE DESPERATELY CRAVES.

11:52.540 --> 11:55.907
AGENTS,
I'M SANDRA MADSEN.

11:55.940 --> 11:57.373
I'M THE NEWS
DIRECTOR HERE.

11:57.410 --> 11:59.378
WHAT CAN I DO
FOR YOU?

11:59.410 --> 12:01.878
IS THERE SOMEPLACE
WE CAN TALK?

12:01.920 --> 12:03.410
SURE. FOLLOW ME.

12:03.450 --> 12:04.849
BACK TO WORK,
EVERYONE.

12:04.890 --> 12:07.779
WE CAN TALK OVER HERE.

12:07.820 --> 12:10.983
I'VE NEVER HAD A VISIT
FROM THE FBI BEFORE.

12:11.030 --> 12:12.520
IT MUST BE
IMPORTANT.

12:12.560 --> 12:14.949
HOW CAN I HELP
YOU, AGENTS?

12:15.000 --> 12:17.764
WELL, WE SAW YOUR REPORT
ON THE MATCHING CLIPS

12:17.800 --> 12:19.290
FOUND IN THE FEMALE
VICTIMS' HAIR.

12:19.330 --> 12:20.968
THAT WAS GREAT WORK.

